definitions.definition: An exchange of two comparable things.
( finance ) A financial derivative in which two parties agree to exchange one stream of non-normal cashflow against another stream.
( computing , informal , uncountable ) Space available in a swap file for use as auxiliary memory .
examples: How much swap do you need?

definitions.definition: ( Cambridge University slang ) A social meal at a restaurant between two university societies , usually involving drinking and banter ; commonly associated with fining and pennying ; equivalent to a crewdate at Oxford University .
